  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In COPD the patient's ability to use inhalers correctly and their preference for the inhaler
      are both important factors in selecting an appropriate treatment for COPD. This  is a
      cross-sectional study where satisfaction, preference and handling of two different devices
      such as Respimat and Breezhaler will be evaluated by using the validated PASAPQ in COPD
      patients
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
