    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion criteria:

          1. All patients must sign an informed consent consistent with International Conference
             on Harmonization - Good Clinical Practice (ICH-GCP) guidelines prior to participation
             in the study and conducting any study procedures.

          2. Adult male or female patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) for
             less than a year who follow usual clinical practice of the participant sites and who
             are on treatment with Spiriva® Respimat®, Hirobriz® Breezhaler® / Onbrez® Breezhaler®
             / Oslif® Breezhaler® for at least of 3 months but not more than maximum of 6 months
             before the informed consent date.

        Exclusion criteria:

          1. Previously included in this study or currently participating in another
             interventional study.

          2. Visual, cognitive, or motor impairment that as judged by the investigator does not
             allow the patient to independently read and complete the questionnaire.

          3. Patients who are treated simultaneously with both respiratory medications (Spiriva®
             Respimat® and Hirobriz® Breezhaler® / Onbrez® Breezhaler® / Oslif® Breezhaler®).
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
